T1  - A Characterization of Game-Theoretic Solutions Which Lead to Impossibility Theorems
PY  - 1996
Y1  - 1996/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298113
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 63
IS  - 1
SP  - 23
EP  - 38
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - For some game-theoretic solution concepts, such as dominant strategies, Nash equilibrium, and undominated strategies, only dictatorial social choice functions are implementable on a full domain of preferences with at least three alternatives. For other solution concepts, such as the iterative removal of weakly dominated strategies, undominated Nash equilibrium, and maximin, it is possible to implement non-dictatorial social choice functions. Which aspects of solution concepts accounts for these differences? We answer this question by providing a characterization of solution concepts which lead to impossibility results.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298113
ER  - 



